Definition: inclined to or conducive to companionship with others
Example: a sociable occasion; enjoyed a sociable chat; a sociable conversation; Americans are sociable and gregarious
Synonyms: noun, group, sociable, attribute, sociableness, sociability, UNSOCIABLE, EXTROVERSIVE, FRIENDLY, SOCIAL, inclined, to, or, conducive, companionship, with, others, a, occasion, enjoyed, chat, conversation, Americans, are, and, gregarious
Category: adj.all
